<i>Posted by Brisbanoch on 11-28-2001 06:06 AM:</i>

<p><b> 
</b></p>

<p>I'm not pissed, i'm disappointed the company is putting priority on wimping classes over fixing major parts of the game that are out right broken. <br />
<br />
Pallys using refresh and twisting chants weren't over powered solo, the only time they were really overpowered is in multiple pally groups, if they were all twisting heal chants.<br />
<br />
I can think of exactly 3 mobs that i could solo when they were 1 level orange, using twisting chants. I can think of even con yellows that would kill me no matter how much I twisted. That sounds like it fits into the general assessment of class balance. Now, most yellows will likely kill me, although i can probably do most lower ones.<br />
<br />
I think it took a fun, balanced class, and powered it down a significant amount. I could think of a half dozen other classes (three that solo reds) that could have used a bit of tuning first, and I could think of a few classes that could have used some unnerfing to actually be useful.<br />
<br />
I think Mythic needs to hire a few more people to work on important stuff, so it doesn't look like they are just trying to piss classes off.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
