<i>Posted by Terrak on 11-28-2001 03:35 PM:</i>

<p><b> 
</b></p>

<p>For the love of Christ, stop calling it a nerf!  The stuff with Chants was a known and documented bug during Beta!  It needed to be fixed and fixed soon.  You know why?  Because I remember a number of times that Verant pulled BS where long after (sometimes a year or two) release announced that something commonly believed to be a tactic was actually a bug.  I personally would rather see this bug fixed sooner than later as I was already seeing a disturbing number of Paladins who believed that it was a feature.  I've lived through the stigma of being a Ranger when their whining was at their (previous) worst; I don't want to have to go through the same with Paladins because somehow everything should take a higher priority than fixing this bug and it gets viewed as a nerf a year later.<br />
<br />
Now, that said, are there other classes that need attention?  Of course there are.  Are they being ignored?  No, but instant gratification isn't always the way of the world.  Were infiltrators blown off so that Paladin chants could be changed?  No, their issues are handled by different folks.  Jim the spell guy works on (surprise) spells.<br />
<br />
All issues will be dealt with but just because a bug gets fixed in one class doesn't mean that the issues of another class are being ignored.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
